    • print_weekly_appointments

      public void print_weekly_appointments​(java.lang.String username, java.lang.String startDate, java.lang.String endDate, java.lang.String month, java.lang.String year) throws java.sql.SQLException, java.io.FileNotFoundException
      This function opens a dialog to take a path from user , where the file will be stored.

      It will read the appointments of the selected week and write them into the file one by one.

      Parameters:
      username - profile that is logged in currently.
      startDate - Date on the start of the week.
      endDate - Date on the end of the week.
      month - Month of the selected week.
      year - Year of the selected week-
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - errors which occur in the sql connection and commands.
      java.io.FileNotFoundException - if the files is missing.
